We Believe Dancers Should Perform. Please Help Us Make It Happen! The point of studying ballet is to perform. It is performing that gives students the confidence they need to compete or to succeed in a professional career of any kind. Stage experience enables students to develop grace, confidence, and stage etiquette.The Only Thing Holding Us Back Is FinancesJaelyn Fellona, IBT Director:"Between securing the venue, paying for guest artists and promotion materials, production costs for Nutcracker add up quickly. It takes incredible amount of time, dedication, and patience on part of our Artistic Director and our talented students to produce a show. And yet, none of it is enough if finances are not in place. In the past we struggled to produce full-length ballets on very little resources. But if we keep doing it, the company will simply go broke."IBT Has Talented Students and Exceptional TeachersOur kids study to become professional ballet dancers. IBT students, who are part of the company, have rigorous schedule: they dance for 20 (twenty) or more hours per week and spend numerous extra hours rehearsing for professional-level performances. These kids sacrifice a lot to dance and put their whole hearts into dancing. Trained in the famous Vaganova Syllabus (Russian Classical Ballet Method,) they study Ballet, Pointe, Variations, Partnering, Character Folk Dance, Contemporary, Stretch, Ballet History, and Russian language. All of these classes are graded and leveled. IBT regularly participate in prestigious classical ballet competitions, such as Youth America Grand Prix, Tanzolymp Berlin, Arabesque Perm, Russia, American Ballet Competition, and World Balker Competition in Florida. In addition, they are coached by Guest Teachers from Boston Ballet and Mariinsky Ballet (ex-Kirov Ballet of St. Petersburg, Russia). IBT would value your contribution, no matter how small! Your donation is tax deductible!* Please help us by

sharing this video and campaign on Facebook and Twitter;


emailing friends who you think would support our cause;


spreading the word about our amazing company and students.

THANK YOU!* IBT: HELP US PERFORM is a fiscally sponsored project of International Ballet Theater under the umbrella of Russian-American United Arts Council, a 501(c)(3) nonprofit arts organization. Contributions on behalf of IBT: HELP US Perform are payable to International Ballet Theater and are tax deductible less the value of any goods or/and services received, as allowed by law. After you made your donation please contact IBT to receive your tax deductible donation form.
